headline.main: 14 Japanese Vessels Sighted Heading Toward New Guinea; JAPANESE SIGHTED OFF NEW GUINEA

lead_paragraph: AT UNITED NATIONS HEADQUARTERS, Australia, Tuesday, March 2 -- One of the largest Japanese convoys yet sighted in the northeastern sector of the Southwest Pacific area was reported by the United Nations High Command today to be heading in the direction of New Guinea.
abstract: Bismarck Sea battle: 14 Jap ships sighted off Talasea, New Brit, headed for New Guinea
